				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Dreams of Ayonae<a name="70536"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 2 04 9:58 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>
<br />
I am a 58 bard on the brell server.  Hi
<br />

<br />
Last night I was in a group in Greigs End.  We had a SK(puller and MT), Wiz, Druid, Cleric, Shaman, and Bard(me).  We set up at the gate and were doing well so we decided to move in deeper.
<br />

<br />
The SK pulled a double and I am not sure if someone was too close but when the SK feigned they both came to us.  I mezzed one using Dreams of Ayonae.  These mobs were white and darkblue cons so even the darkblue ones were on the upper level of this song.  I was getting a lot of resist.
<br />

<br />
A few seconds later after I mezzed it the mezz was broken by the druid.  I repulsed the mez and it resisted then finally stuck.  Again mezz broken by druid.  I figure he must have dotted it.  To ad insult to injury he tries to root it.  Druid roots have a damage component so again mezz is broken.  I remezz it.  The whole time I am calling out my mezzes with my hot buttons.
<br />

<br />
Finally the druid falls to his death and the dot runs its course.  I get the mob under control but the other is going on a rampage through the group.  I try to mez it as well but the druid must have dotted it as well before he died becuase I got the group wide message that mezz was broken by his corpse. (kinda funny)
<br />

<br />
I figure we got this thing under control now but I look and I don't see the sk or the shammy.  So the wiz starts to fire off a succor and the cleric begins to melee the second mob that is dotted.  I got the first one locked down in the corner.  Succor goes off and I am somehow left behind even though i was located between the wiz and the cleric.  Stuff happens.
<br />

<br />
Here is my question.  Since DoA has a 30% chance of a memblur would I have been able to pulse them both, invis, run down the hall and see if it stuck on one or both.  If it went on one since I am invis only he would come then i could mezz him and wait for the other to go home then repeat the process?
<br />

<br />
I was in the process of trying when the SK showed up.  Nice of him to try but there were quite mad at me and I was running out of options.  Even though I kept one mezzed the other was to mad at me and he could not get agro before I dropped below 20% so I took the death.  I could have run but that would have meant training a few other groups along the way as well.  
<br />

<br />
What do you guys think?</span></td>
