				<td colspan="2"><span>The memblur effect on DoA is very unreliable. I did use it some in PoN when I was swarming stalkers, say if I got too many spiders and wanted to get one of them out of the pack. I'd do the same thing, run a ways away, mez it and run the pack back to my swarm area, keeping an eye on the mob I wanted to break away... it usually took at least 4 tries though, and you need quite a bit of room to make sure the mobs you do have aggro on doesn't cause social aggro. I applaud you for the quick thinking though. That's what seperates the good bards from the bad bards in most situations.</span></td>
