				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Dreams of Ayonae<a name="70837"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 10 04 2:33 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>2 things that could possibly help you out in future GE groups as a bard.  
<br />

<br />
Number 1, when you first zone in, on the very first creature you find, sing CCC (the faction song).  This will raise you to dubious to everything but Servitor, Grieg, and the wierd shadow guys that you should be nowhere near anyway, so you personally don't need invis anymore.
<br />

<br />
Number 2, when you are mezzing and trying to see if your memblur kicked in, there are 2 ways to check.
<br />

<br />
-1. If you are in a zone which you are not kos in (this would be 1 such zone if you used CCC) right after mez hits, con it.  If it's still threatening, it hasn't worked, if it is dubious or better, it has worked, stop the song before you piss it off again. This is the easy way.
<br />

<br />
-2. If you are in a zone that you are KOS in, pay close attention after each tick to see if the creature says it's &quot;battlecry&quot;  This is what they say when they are first aggro'd and they will say it again each time you mez after a successful memblur.  The downside is it's near impossible to use this to save yourself, but if you do it right it will at least save the rest of your group allowing them to move out of aggro range in case you have lots of resists and you know that eventually it will break free and eat someone, this way it might be just you instead of the whole grp.  The only part of this that I'm not 100% certain on is if they say something after being hit again after the memblur or because of the memblur and therefore saying you are safe.  If you are in a solo situation hoping for mez to save you, try it out, if you hear them talk, stop song and back away waiting for mez to break, the worst that can happen is you have to remez it (hopefully).
<br />

<br />
I gotta say, I wasn't a huge fan of Dreams of Ayonae, cuz at least for me, when I got it, I wasn't a raider at the time, so it was far from common, and all it did was raise the mez cap like 2 lvls from the previous song.  Luckily you should be getting a new mez soon tho.  Anyway, good luck in GE.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
